    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - Meritor Medium Duty Front Drive Steer Axle - Lubrication, Inspection and
        Maintenance - Steering Knuckle Sockets
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="lubricate" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Steering Knuckle Sockets</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Verify that the tires touch the ground. DO NOT RAISE THE VEHICLE.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean grease fitting prior to lubrication.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lube the knuckle sockets through the grease fittings on the top and bottom knuckle caps
                (Figure 71).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0201271" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg02/G0201271.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 71. Lube Knuckle Sockets</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. UPPER GREASE (ZERK) FITTING</callout1>
                <callout1>2. LOWER GREASE (ZERK) FITTING</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Force lubricant into the upper and lower knuckle sockets until lubricant flows out between
                the axle housing sockets and the steering knuckle.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
